benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion Scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04): removing all tags or a subset from an invoice item with 204 and an empty body
Non-Existent Resource (TC08): 404 for a non-existent invoice item
Input Validation and Error Handling (TC09, TC10, TC11, TC13, TC15, TC16): coverage for invalid UUID, missing header, invalid token, malformed tagDef, header injections, and partial tagDef inputs
TagDef Parameter Coverage (TC02, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC13, TC14, TC16): variations including subset, empty, non-present IDs, extra parameters, very large lists, and malformed values
Edge Case Handling and Data Integrity (TC04, TC05, TC18): removal when item has no tags, removal when some tags are not on the item, and special characters in headers
Performance and Concurrency (TC17): high-concurrency delete scenarios
Integration and Availability (TC12, TC19): service down and audit-logging unavailable
gaps: Soft Deletes: no explicit test validating soft-delete semantics for tag removals
403 Forbidden scenario: no test specifically verifying access when the user lacks permission
Rate Limiting: no tests for rate limiting/throttling on DELETE requests
Caching Behavior: no tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation on delete
Pagination: not applicable to this endpoint but not covered for large datasets in general
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden scenario test to cover insufficient permissions for tag removal
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to evaluate behavior under burst DELETE requests
Add caching header tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and cache invalidation validation
Include a dedicated test to verify soft-delete semantics if applicable
